# Sentinel Ensemble — environment template
# Copy this file to `.env` (same folder) and paste your real key:
#     cp .env.example .env
# `.env` is gitignored and is read automatically at launch (the value is never
# printed, logged, or persisted anywhere else). You can also just
# `export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...`, or paste it at the hidden prompt on first run.

# Your Anthropic API key (https://console.anthropic.com -> API keys).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️  API USAGE TIER — IMPORTANT
# The analysis stage runs a 4-MODEL ENSEMBLE in parallel (4 concurrent API
# calls), plus the other invocations. A Tier-1 account ($5) is likely to hit
# rate limits (HTTP 429) on those parallel calls.
#   • Tier 1  ($5)   — fine for `--demo`; will rate-limit the live ensemble
#   • Tier 2  ($40)  — recommended minimum for a full live run
#   • Tier 3  ($200) — smoothest (no throttling on parallel calls)
# Your tier auto-increases with account age + spend; check it at
# console.anthropic.com -> Plans & Billing.
# (Optional) Use a smaller/faster model tier to reduce cost — pick "2" (Haiku)
# at the depth prompt, or the ensemble can be narrowed via SIFT_ENSEMBLE_MODELS.
